{"article_id":"xlwnABadhhlHpXMH","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama 's campaign continues to hammer presumptive Republican nominee Mitt Romney over the GOP challenger 's refusal","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to release more of his tax returns .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Romney has provided one year 's record","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and promised a second year 's worth of returns .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"But even some of his fellow Republicans now say","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that 's not enough .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Obama 's campaign launched a new TV ad this week ,","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"shining a spotlight on what is and is n't known about Romney 's taxes ,","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"asking ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"`` What is Mitt Romney hiding ? ''","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"So far , Romney and his family trusts have released their 2010 tax returns ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"which fill hundreds of pages .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"He got an extension for his 2011 return","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"and has promised to release that","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"as soon as it 's ready ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"no later than mid-October .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"`` People always want to get more .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"We 're putting out what 's required , plus more , ''","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"he said last week on CNN .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"`` Those are the two years","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that people will have ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"and that 's all","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that 's necessary","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"for people to understand something about my finances . ''","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"But tax professionals still have plenty of questions .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"For example , Lee Sheppard , a contributing editor at the journal Tax Notes , wants to know","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"how Romney amassed so much money in his tax-deferred retirement account .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"`` All","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"we know","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"is really that it 's a big number ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"and we 're a little bit baffled","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"as to how it got so big , ''","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Sheppard says .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Candidates list their assets in broad ranges ,","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"so we know","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Romney 's retirement account is worth somewhere between $ 21 million and $ 102 million .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Law professor Ed Kleinbard of the University of Southern California says","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"that 's a lot of money","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"considering the most","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"Romney could ever contribute to the account","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"was $ 30,000 a year .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"`` Either Gov . Romney is sort of the modern-day equivalent of Jack and his magic beans ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"who somehow created a mighty beanstalk ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"or he took a very aggressive position with respect to valuing insider stock , ''","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Kleinbard says .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Kleinbard means","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"that Romney might have loaded up his retirement account with assets from his private equity firm , Bain Capital ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"and assigned artificially low values to those assets","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"in order to get around the federal contribution limits .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"If so ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Romney would still have to pay taxes on the real value of the assets","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"when they 're withdrawn from the account .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"But in the meantime , the money can grow tax-free .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"Tax Notes '","depth":4},{"id":54,"text":"Sheppard says","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"that 's an advantage","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"most taxpayers do n't have .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"`` If you happen to work for a partnership","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"and your compensation is arranged this way ,","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"you get this very beneficial treatment , ''","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Sheppard says .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Romney 's campaign did n't respond to NPR 's questions about his retirement account .","depth":3},{"id":62,"text":"But his taxes have been dogging the candidate since the GOP primary .","depth":4},{"id":63,"text":"At an NBC debate in January , Romney argued","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"that there 's nothing wrong","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"with minimizing taxes .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"`` I pay all the taxes","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that are legally required","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and not a dollar more , ''","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"you want someone as the candidate for president","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"who pays more taxes","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"than he owes . ''","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Romney was equally aggressive toward taxes in the business world .","depth":5},{"id":75,"text":"For years , he was a director of Marriott International , the hotel company","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"founded by Willard Marriott .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"Kleinbard ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"who worked on Wall Street","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"and served as chief of staff for Congress ' Joint Committee on Taxation ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"says","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Marriott had a reputation .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"`` Marriott was always a tax shelter promoter 's first call , ''","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"he says .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"`` Marriott was one of those companies","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"that just loved to buy tax shelters . ''","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"Bloomberg reported this year on one Marriott tax shelter ,","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"known as `` Son of BOSS . ''","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"It involved creating paper losses","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"to offset taxes on real income .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"The Internal Revenue Service challenged the shelter ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"and Marriott lost in court .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"Judges called the shelter `` fictitious '' and a `` scheme , ''","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"and the company was forced to pay $ 29 million .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Kleinbard notes","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"when the shelter was adopted ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"Romney was the chairman of Marriott 's audit committee .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"`` It 's the job of the chair of the audit committee of Marriott to say ,","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"'Hey , wait a minute ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"just because we have an opinion from Winkin ' , Blinkin ' and Nod","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"that this is a terribly clever idea ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"I need to apply some common sense","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"as opposed to just signing on the bottom line , ' ``","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Kleinbard says .","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"A statement from Marriott says","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"the company only engages in tax deals","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"it believes","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"are lawful .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"`` Marriott only engages in transactions","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"that we believe","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"are in accordance with the tax code","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"and that","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"we think","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"will create shareholder value , ''","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"it said .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Kleinbard sees a pattern for Romney","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"of cutting tax corners .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"Asked about his taxes in that NBC debate ,","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"Romney sidestepped .","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"`` The real question is not so much my taxes , but the taxes of the American people , ''","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"Romney said .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"Romney ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"whose 2010 tax rate was less than 14 percent ,","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"says","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"he wants to overhaul the tax code ,","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"which he calls","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"`` far too complex , '' `` far too intrusive '' and `` far too great . ''","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":257,"left":189,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":138,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":134,"right":137,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":134,"left":130,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":131,"right":132,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":131,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":132,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":137,"left":6,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":7,"right":135,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":135,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":188,"left":180,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":151,"right":179,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":143,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":139,"right":142,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":139,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"